IT seems there’s a new sheriff in town in Christopher Nzimbi.
According to insiders, the Congolese-born businessman and grandson of former president Mobutu Sese Seko “owns” the Joburg and Mzansi nightlife scene.The SunTeam has also witnessed Christopher entertaining the who’s who of Mzansi and popping champagne with them, driving expensive cars, wearing expensive clothes and forever surrounded by a string of ladies wherever he went.if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>But rumour has it that this playboy has a dark secret.This as the government of the Democratic Republic of Congo is said to have given him “a fat tender” of $50 million (about R591 million).With this rumoured money, Christopher was allegedly to build roads in his native country, but was instead said to be blowing it in Mzansi.An informant said he arrived in Mzansi six months after he had failed to fulfil his tender duties in Congo.Said the informant: “Christopher is the kind of man who loves clothing brands, expensive clothes and lives an expensive lifestyle. “He owns houses in Paris and Italy and just recently bought a house in America for $4,5 million. “There’s also a rumour that he had won a Congo tender to build houses there.”The second mole said he loved sending his women to Europe and America to shop in places like Dubai and Las Vegas.“But I’m worried that he spends a lot.”This week, the media-shy Christopher was reluctant to speak to the people’s paper.He said: “I’m a respectable businessman and always provide for the poor and help through my foundation. I’m a giver.”